author: Katy Burne
title: New York Fed Names Supervision Chief
text:
The Federal Reserve Bank of New York named Kevin Stiroh, a 15-year veteran at the bank, as its new head of financial institution supervision, in a leadership transition that emphasizes the bank’s concentration on overhauling a group that had been criticized in recent years.
Mr. Stiroh has a Ph.D. in economics and some private-sector experience, though not at a bank. The regulator was looking for a candidate that hadn’t come directly...
